  "generated_at": "2026-05-03",
  "intent": "Define a vendor-neutral telemetry contract for SecurityRecipes so agentic AI and MCP runs can be reconstructed from OpenTelemetry-shaped traces without leaking secrets, raw tenant context, or unredacted tool payloads into observability systems.",
  "positioning": {
    "buyer": "AI Platform, Security Engineering, Detection Engineering, GRC, model risk, procurement security, and acquisition diligence teams",
    "category": "Agentic AI telemetry contract and secure trace evidence layer",
    "enterprise_promise": "SecurityRecipes makes agent observability reviewable: every governed run must emit enough trace, policy, context, egress, approval, receipt, and redaction evidence for enterprise reviewers to trust the run without reading transcripts.",
    "why_now": "MCP and agent frameworks are standardizing tool calls, handoffs, and GenAI traces at the same time enterprises are discovering that raw prompts, tool arguments, and model outputs can become a new sensitive-data sink. A secure context layer needs a trace contract that is useful to defenders and safe for regulated environments."
  },
